---
alwaysApply: true
---
  PROJECT STRUCTURE (SIMPLE)
- Keep UI, logic, and services separate.
- Do not mix business logic inside widgets.
- Keep files small and easy to understand.

---

  STATE MANAGEMENT (SIMPLE RULE)
- Use only ONE state management approach.
- Keep state outside UI when possible.
- Avoid complex architectures.
- Simple is better than scalable overkill.

---

  THEME RULES
- Always use AppColors (no direct Colors.*)
- Keep theme usage simple.
- Do not create complex theme systems.
- Support dark mode in a basic way only.

---

  LOCALIZATION
- Use localized text only for UI strings.
- Keep it simple.
- No complex translation logic.

---

  WIDGET RULES
- Prefer StatelessWidget.
- Keep widgets small.
- Avoid deep nesting.
- Extract widgets only when needed.

---

  PERFORMANCE (BASIC)
- Use const when easy.
- Avoid unnecessary rebuilds.
- Use ListView.builder for lists.

---

  ASYNC RULES
- Always handle errors simply.
- Show loading and error states.
- Do not put heavy async logic inside widgets.

---

  DEPENDENCIES
- Do not add packages without reason.
- Prefer Flutter built-in tools first.

---

  CODE STYLE
- Write clear variable names.
- Avoid abbreviations.
- No unused or dead code.
- Keep code readable for beginners.

---

  TESTING MINDSET
- Keep logic separate from UI.
- Write code that is easy to understand and test.

---

  SECURITY
- Never hardcode secrets or keys.
- Keep user data safe and simple.

---

  OUTPUT RULE
- Code must always compile.
- Keep solutions beginner friendly.
- No advanced architecture unless asked.